beginParachainDispute(bytes32,uint256,by.details: Start dispute/vote for a specific parachain // Trusts that the corresponding value for the supplied query identifier and timestamp // exists on the consumer parachain, that it has been removed during dispute initiation, // and that a dispute fee has been locked.

params._disputeInitiator: address Initiator who started the dispute/proposal
params._disputedReporter: address Reporter who submitted the disputed value
params._queryId: bytes32 Query ID of disputed value
params._slashAmount: uint256 Amount of tokens to be slashed of staker

params._teamMultiSig: address of tellor team multisig, one of four voting stakeholder groups

didVote(bytes32,address).details: Determines if an address voted for a specific vote

params._disputeId: is the ID of the vote
params._voter: is the address of the voter to check for

returns._0: bool of whether or note the address voted for the specific vote

executeVote(bytes32).details: Executes vote and transfers corresponding balances to initiator/reporter

params._disputeId: is the ID of the vote being executed

getDisputeInfo(bytes32).details: Returns info on a dispute for a given ID

params._disputeId: is the ID of a specific dispute

returns._0: bytes32 of the data ID of the dispute
returns._1: uint256 of the timestamp of the dispute
returns._2: bytes memory of the value being disputed
returns._3: address of the reporter being disputed

getVoteInfo(bytes32,uint8).details: Returns info on a vote for a given vote ID

params._disputeId: is the ID of a specific vote
params._voteRound: is the round of the vote

returns._0: bytes32 identifier hash of the vote
returns._1: uint256[17] memory of the pertinent round info (vote rounds, start date, etc.)
returns._2: bool memory of both whether or not the vote was executed
returns._4: address memory of the vote initiator

getVoteRounds(bytes32).details: Returns an array of voting rounds for a given vote

params._hash: is the identifier hash for a vote (disputeId)

returns._0: uint8 Number of voting rounds for a given disputeId

init(address).details: Allows the owner to initialize the ParachainStaking and token interfaces

tallyVotes(bytes32).details: Tallies the votes and begins the 1 day challenge period

params._disputeId: is the ID of the vote being tallied

vote(bytes32,bool,bool).details: Enables the sender address (staker or multisig) to cast a vote

params._disputeId: is the unique identifier for the dispute
params._supports: is the address's vote: whether or not they support or are against
params._validDispute: is whether or not the dispute is valid (e.g. false if the dispute is invalid)

voteParachain(bytes32,uint256,uint256,ui.details: Enables oracle consumer parachain to cast collated votes of its users and reporters for an open dispute.      This function is called by the oracle consumer parachain, and can be called multiple times.

params._disputeId: is the ID of the dispute
params._totalReportsAgainst: is the total number of reports submitted by reporters who voted against the dispute
params._totalReportsFor: is the total number of reports submitted by reporters who voted for the dispute
params._totalReportsInvalid: is the total number of reports submitted by reporters who voted invalid for the dispute
params._totalTipsAgainst: is the total amount of tips contributed by users who voted against the dispute
params._totalTipsFor: is the total amount of tips contributed by users who voted for the dispute
params._totalTipsInvalid: is the total amount of tips contributed by users who voted invalid for the dispute
